# wrk

> HTTP benchmarking tool
> More information: https://github.com/wg/wrk

- Run a benchmark for `30` seconds, using `12` threads, and keeping `400` HTTP connections open:

`wrk -t{int number: 12} -c{int number: 400} -d{any something} "{any something}"`

- Run a benchmark with a custom header:

`wrk -t{int number: 2} -c{int number: 5} -d{any something} -H "{any something}"â€Š"{any something}"`

- Run a benchmark with a request timeout of `2` seconds:

`wrk -t{int number: 2} -c{int number: 5} -d{any something} --timeout {any something} "{any something}"`
